
                                            Makhura says Chiba’s impact on the South African revolution was profound and his name is synonymous with discipline and leadership. 
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura has sent his condolences to the family of struggle stalwart Laloo Chiba following his death yesterday. Makhura says Chiba’s impact on the South African revolution was profound and his name is synonymous with discipline and leadership. Chiba suffered a heart attack a few days ago and was hospitalised, before being discharged. Makhura says Chiba was a gracious, self-effacing and compassionate man. His spokesperson Phumla Sekhonyane said, “The premier says he’s saddened by the passing of the veteran.”